> This hearty vegetarian soup is packed with two types of plant-based protein—lentils and beans—and loads of veggies. Tender lentils simmer with carrots, celery, and onion in a delicately spiced vegetable broth, and kidney beans add body and richness. Serve with a dollop of sour cream and chopped chives for a final flourish.

Wash and dry produce. Halve, peel, and dice @onion{1}(halved, peeled, and diced into 1/2-inch pieces). Trim, peel, and halve @carrots{6%ounce}(trimmed and halved lengthwise; sliced crosswise into 1/4-inch half-moons). Halve @celery{2.5%ounce}(halved lengthwise and thinly sliced crosswise into pieces). Drain and rinse @lentils{1%unit}.

In a #medium pot{}, heat a large drizzle of @cooking oil{} over medium-high heat. Add onion, carrots, celery, @salt{}, and @pepper{}; cook, stirring occasionally, until veggies are slightly softened, ~{2-3%minutes}.

Add @garlic powder{1%teaspoon}, @chili powder{1%teaspoon}, @cumin{1%teaspoon}, and @tomato paste{1%unit}; cook, stirring, until fragrant, ~{30-60%seconds}.

Stir in @water{2 1/2%cups}, lentils, and @veggie stock concentrate{3%unit}, scraping up any browned bits from bottom of #pot{}. Bring to a simmer; cook, uncovered, until slightly reduced, ~{5-7%minutes}.

Meanwhile, empty @kidney beans{1%unit} and their liquid into a #medium bowl{}. Mash with a #potato masher{} or fork until beans are mostly smooth (this will help thicken the soup).

Once soup has simmered ~{5-7%minutes}, stir mashed beans into soup. Return to a boil, then reduce to a simmer. Cook, stirring occasionally, until soup thickens, ~{3-5%minutes} more. Taste and season with salt and pepper if desired.

While soup simmers, thinly slice @chives{1/4%ounce}.

Divide soup between bowls. Dollop with @sour cream{3%tablespoon} and sprinkle with chives. Serve.